column1: short story: a new york plot twist

column2: haunted by an attack that i experienced in chicago
column3: i felt trapped in my own body
column5: even dissociated from my physical body. at the time
column6: there was no #metoo movement & sharing my trauma often led to more questions
column7: “why me?” “why didn’t i stay home that night?” jostled by my own fear that it is my fault because i made the wrong decisions that night
column8: i stated to question every decision i’ve ever made in my entire life. “i must be stupid. maybe if i had stayed in school an extra year and finished my criminal justice degree instead of just the other 2 degrees i graduated with
column9: i would be working in law enforcement
column10: ” i thought. “maybe i’d be a fed. why did i study english and psychology anyway? if i had studied something more practical
column11: i wouldn’t have had to attend that other school to switch my career to health care later. i wouldn’t have met that ta and he wouldn’t have raped me and i wouldn’t feel like this. it’s my fault.” i spend days upon days
column12: analyzing and rehashing every decision until one day on the set of empire
column13: i met a beautiful russian model named anna
column14: “but you do belong here. you are an artist. things can turn around. you are in this place because you have talents no one else does.” at the time
column15: i didn’t feel like much of an artist dragging my crap from set to set
column16: working background on shows. i did not even want to be an actress. it just happened. after reporting my rape
column17: i had to move and leave my job working for a medical group out of fear my offender would find me.  i was living off my credit cards for a while just to survive and buy food and i stumbled on some extra work because it was available and i felt safe around security and cameras. on sets i felt safe. “go back to school
column19: ” my friend carmilla encouraged me. “go to new york
column21: get inspired. you’re an amazing writer
column22: find a program and a mentor to help you with that.” with almost no plan
column23: i got a plane ticket & took my chances with new york
column24: for inspiration. this decision altered my life.";;en;#NewYork

column1: unser körper stellt sich langsam um
column2: wird träger. das bedürfnis nach ruhe und stille nimmt zu. für viele dinge brauchen wir mehr anlaufzeit als sonst. morgens würden wir vielleicht gerne etwas länger schlafen
column3: endlich mal wieder ausschlafen. die jahreszeitliche energie des beginnenden novembers bringt eine entschleunigung mit sich und unterstützt den rückzug in die innenwelt. in der natur gibt es kaum noch ablenkungen
column4: die vielfalt finden wir jetzt in der beschäftigung mit uns selbst. gefühle wie trauer
column9: wut oder gar hass dürfen jetzt voll erlebt und alle stationen durchlaufen werden: es geht um anschauen
column11: ausdrücken und loslassen. nimm dir bei bedarf jetzt die zeit
column13: wie sehr dich bestimmte veränderungen in den letzten monaten bewegt haben und dein leben beeinträchtigt haben. die systemische familientherapie ist eine moderne form des uralten wissens
column14: dass eigenschaften und kräfte aus der ahnenlinie in jedem von uns weiterleben. was in früheren kulturen intuitiv wahrgenommen wurde
column15: hat sich heute in eine therapeutische zugangsweise verwandelt
column16: die den bewussten umgang mit familienthemen anbietet. samhain ist der ideale zeitpunkt
column17: generationsübergreifend würdigung und achtung in das familiensystem zu bringen
column18: jedem und allem einen passenden platz zu geben und damit störungen
column20: aufzulösen. deine fragen für dein samhain ritual: wofür möchte ich insgesamt nochmal dankbar sein im rückblick auf die letzten monate? was hat mich dieses jahr besonders beschäftigt oder sogar belastet? welche wünsche und vorhaben haben sich nicht meinen vorstellungen gemäß erfüllt? für welche themen benötige ich noch mehr zeit
column21: um sie zu lösen?  was hat mich geschwächt? waren es krankheiten? [siehe kommentar] dein lab.danum

no toca ningún instrumento pero tiene pendiente aprender algún día piano.

we are living in a very interesting time with regards to masculinity. the word itself is changing
column2: doing its damndest to evolve out of the definition that has contained it for centuries: “the qualities typically associated with being a man.” that simplistic view is far too minimal to encapsulate the full emotional spectrum of what it is to be a man in today’s society. it is the reason so much is ignored or misunderstood when it comes to our role as men in creating and understanding a holistic masculinity.

we are living in a very interesting time with regards to masculinity. the word itself is changing
column2: doing its damndest to evolve out of the definition that has contained it for centuries: “the qualities typically associated with being a man.” that simplistic view is far too minimal to encapsulate the full emotional spectrum of what it is to be a man in today’s society. it is the reason so much is ignored or misunderstood when it comes to our role as men in creating and understanding a holistic masculinity.

column1: 267208;instagram;2018-10-30 13:36:34;FALSE;"for somebody. from my heart to yours ❤️ pick up the phone!  mend it while you have time.  i went to mommys yesterday to pick out her outfit for her service on saturday. i kept expecting her to come out of one of those rooms and hug me or kiss my cheek.
i imagined that we would talk
column2: laugh or maybe i would brush her hair or massage her scalp. then it hit me that i would never see my mommy again. not in the physical at least. yet my heart even though it is broken
column3: smiles because i have no regrets. we were on good terms
column4: better than we had ever been because i picked up the phone and made it right. i told pride to get tf away from me and did what my heart desired. perhaps there is someone out here that needs to do the same thing. i say do it while there is still time because once someone is gone. that's it. there are no do overs! no rewinding! i can't imagine how i would feel if my mommy was gone and we never got the chance to fix it. i am praying for whomever needs to do the same. that's a weight i would never want to carry and i would never want you to either. i love you fam‼️be blessed! ❤️ #lovemovement #lovetrumpshate365 #playwright #host #brandambassador #healer #actress #activist #motivationalspeaker #domesticviolence #rape #abuse #metoo

column1: 267214;instagram;2018-10-30 12:50:56;FALSE;"did you know that i'm a total crier? like
column2: i legit. cry about everything! good or bad! i'm crying! sad
column5: scared... i'm going to cry about it! don't even try to sit through an episode of america's got talent with me 😭😭 #waterworks .

column1: did you also know that all my life
column2: i've just been trying to be part of a #girlgang that accepted me for who i am!? yup. you read that right... all i've ever wanted to do in life is like save the world with a bunch of my girlfriends!👩‍❤️‍👩 that's why i was pulled to cheerleading rather than just gymnastics back in my younger years... it was the team aspect that i yearned for... that's why i played volleyball
column3: and ran around with 'the fab four' senior year of high school (you know who you are 😉) i lived with seven girls in one house in college at ohio university; and even minored in women and gender studies... where the majority of my classes were based around gender and women equality💕and even after that i always worked in female dominated industries! i worked at hair salons
column5: massage studios and even an all female dental office!! i think it's safe to say that women
column6: are my people! i get women
column7: and i'm not afraid to admit that. i noticed it may be taboo to say that these days. but i'm here to tell you
column8: i am most definitely not embarrassed! ladies
column9: we need each other! we need to uplift one another. i found myself crying recently (true story) about women oppression... about how we are rising above it and no longer standing for it! the whole #metoo movement just makes me so proud of us
column10: and i am in aww that i get to live and breathe during this time! the 4th wave feminist movement is happening
column11: and its a new generation of women empowerment and it just gets me excited to even be part of!! .

column1: so my goal? use this movement

column7: jill captures the zeitgeist of a generation with thoughtful and revolutionary ideas about gender

column1: 【 美國期中選舉：民主制度之挑戰？ 】
題目：the u.s. midterm elections: is democracy at stake?
研究領域：國際政治經濟、國際關係理論、外交政策分析
經歷：日內瓦國際關係及發展學院 國際關係及政治科學學系教授
∙ 教授認為此次期中選舉是美國有史以來最關鍵的一場選舉，將於下週二選出435席眾議員、34席參議員及39州的州長。儘管川普不受大眾歡迎，共和黨仍佔有此次選舉優勢，34席參議員中現任為民主黨的有26席，眾議員自2010年也有明顯的傑利蠑螈現象，且歷年期中選舉民主黨票源 (年輕人、少數族群) 投票率都較低。
∙ 選舉預測： 共和黨有超過 80% 的機率拿下參議院席次；民主黨則有 85% 機率拿下眾議院席次；州長選舉方面，共和黨可望拿下17州(人數較少的州)、民主黨15州、3州搖擺州。
∙ 值得關注的焦點為往年普遍支持共和黨的鄉村白人女性，在近期 #metoo 風波後，是否仍會投給共和黨。另外，多數共和黨選民並非支持川普，而是因為他們共同厭惡民主黨。

column1: 【 美國期中選舉：民主制度之挑戰？ 】
題目：the u.s. midterm elections: is democracy at stake?
研究領域：國際政治經濟、國際關係理論、外交政策分析
經歷：日內瓦國際關係及發展學院 國際關係及政治科學學系教授
∙ 教授認為此次期中選舉是美國有史以來最關鍵的一場選舉，將於下週二選出435席眾議員、34席參議員及39州的州長。儘管川普不受大眾歡迎，共和黨仍佔有此次選舉優勢，34席參議員中現任為民主黨的有26席，眾議員自2010年也有明顯的傑利蠑螈現象，且歷年期中選舉民主黨票源 (年輕人、少數族群) 投票率都較低。
∙ 選舉預測： 共和黨有超過 80% 的機率拿下參議院席次；民主黨則有 85% 機率拿下眾議院席次；州長選舉方面，共和黨可望拿下17州(人數較少的州)、民主黨15州、3州搖擺州。
∙ 值得關注的焦點為往年普遍支持共和黨的鄉村白人女性，在近期 #metoo 風波後，是否仍會投給共和黨。另外，多數共和黨選民並非支持川普，而是因為他們共同厭惡民主黨。

column1: - i’m honest about #ptsd and the recovery i’m going through from being sexually assaulted because i believe it matters - not because i want anyone to feel sorry for me. i want people to know that while it’s brutal and raw
column2: it can be done. and you can feel better. you just have to do the work. for me? it’s intensive 2-3 days a week where i rehash things i’d rather forget (and things i avoided for over 15 years)
column3: but everyday i learn something new. if you’re struggling
column4: i want you to know you’re not alone. ⠀

column1: 267380;instagram;2018-10-30 10:37:19;FALSE;"qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv
column2: completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

column1: that’s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him “we can take it.” no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it’s a little thing
column2: just part of the story we are all interacting with.

column1: the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters
column2: then it’s easy to come along for the ride. there’s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they’re both just characters on the television.

column1: that’s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it’s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it’s that we’ve lost the capacity to treat civics
column3: and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters
column4: so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

column1: 267406;instagram;2018-10-30 09:52:35;FALSE;"this year @thatsarahscott reported to @sagaftra how her costar #kippardue put her hand on his groin then instead of apologizing in his trailer like she thought he would masturbated in front of her.

not only does kip admit to the groin incident (denies trailer incident) but when sarah reported this to sag-aftra they sat on this for 6 months only to release a statement yesterday saying ""keep members names confidential when things like this happen."" what??? i'm discouraged and disappointed that after harvey weinstein and other men have been accused in the past of sexual harassment and assault the new process is to deal w it privately. how about deal w it quickly? saddest part is a woman is the head of that union currently.  kinda makes me wanna stay away from acting.

acting/screenwriting has been a goal of mine since i was 17. been writing and taking acting classes towards that goal. now knowing a union i'll be a part of may not protect me has completely changed my mind about pursuing. as a black transwoman what will happen if i'm assaulted or harassed? will this union protect me?

column1: 267436;instagram;2018-10-30 09:08:03;FALSE;"wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014
column2: when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

column1: documents show the john bolton super pac
column2: which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton
column4: 700 in 2014 for ""behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging."" those services included strategies that broke individual voters into ""clusters"" based on what messages would resonate with them.

column1: 267473;instagram;2018-10-30 08:17:23;FALSE;"♦️چه چیزی در ⁧ #من_هم ⁩ مردان را ترسانده و این جنبش چه تغییری را در مردان به وجود آورده است؟ ✍برگرفته از توییتر فرانک عمیدی 📌داشتن برتری جنسی و فیزیکی به این معنی بوده که مردان نباید به این فکر میکردن که رفتار و گفتارشون چه حسی در زنان ایجاد میکنه چون سورفتار هزینه ای براشون نداشته. برعکس زنان. در روابط جنسی مثلا زنان همیشه باید خودشان را جای مردان میگذاشتن: نکنه عصبانی بشه، نکنه کاری کنم که متوسل به زور بشه. نکنه حرکتم باعث بشه فکر کنه مردانگیش زیر سوال رفته. چه جوری به او نه بگویم که کارم را از دست ندم. چه جوری بهش جواب رد بدم که بعدا آبروم را نبره. برای همه اینها زنان باید خودشون را تا حدودی جای مردان میذاشتن چون در غیر این صورت باید هزینه پرداخت میکردن اما چنین چیزی لزوما برای مردان صدق نمیکرده. مردان چون از جایگاه اجتماعی و اقتصادی بالاتری نسبت به زنان برخوردار بودن در چنین مواردی نباید چندان نگران این میبودن که زنان چه حسی نسبت به رفتارشان دارن. مثلا یک مدیر مرد در یک شرکت با فراغ خاطر میتونسته کارمند زن را آزارجنسی بده

این کارمند زن بوده که باید فکر میکرده چه جوری واکنش بدم که کارم را از دست ندم، نکنه واکنشم باعث بشه عصبانی بشه و غیره در حالیکه برای آن مرد که در جایگاه قدرت بوده تنها چیز مهم به دست آوردن خواستش بوده. اتفاقی که با جنبشی مثل  #metoo  افتاد این بود که حالا مردان باید به این فکر کنن که رفتار و گفتارشون چه حسی را در زنان ایجاد میکنه. حالا مردها باید خودشان را جای زنان بگذارن وگرنه باید هزینه بدن. این نگرانی از هزینه دادن در اینکه ما مجبور باشیم خودمون را کمی جای دیگران بذاریم تاثیر زیادی داره.

دیگه فقط مهم نیست که اونچه که میخوای را بگیری بلکه اینکه چه جوری اون را گرفتی و طرف با چه حسی خواسته تو را برآورده کرده مهم میشه. این یه تغییر بزرگ در روابط زن و مرد به طور گسترده ایجاد میکنه. اینکه مردان حالا باید یاد بگیرن که این چیزها را در نظر بگیرن خیلی گام بزرگیه و برای مردان هم خوبه. این فقط زنان نیستن که ازین مسئله سود میبرن این هوش عاطفی و حساسیت به احساسات طرف مقابل داینامیک روابط انسانی را بهتر میکنه.

* مسلما وقتی از مردان و زنان حرف میزنم منظورم این نیست همه مردان و همه زنان اینجورین و مردها همه آزاردهنده جنسی و زنان همه قربانی بودن. بلکه منظورم اون تجربه زیستی زن و مرد هست که یک میانگین رفتار و واکنش را ایجاد میکنه در جوامع.

'NNP'), ('جوامع', 'NNP'), ('.', '.'), ('مینیسم', 'NN'), ('eminismeveryday', 'NN')];♦️چه چیزی در ⁧ ⁩ مردان را ترسانده و این جنبش چه تغییری را در مردان به وجود آورده است؟ ✍برگرفته از توییتر فرانک عمیدی 📌داشتن برتری جنسی و فیزیکی به این معنی بوده که مردان نباید به این فکر میکردن که رفتار و گفتارشون چه حسی در زنان ایجاد میکنه چون سورفتار هزینه ای براشون نداشته . برعکس زنان . در روابط جنسی مثلا زنان همیشه باید خودشان را جای مردان میگذاشتن : نکنه عصبانی بشه، نکنه کاری کنم که متوسل به زور بشه . نکنه حرکتم باعث بشه فکر کنه مردانگیش زیر سوال رفته . چه جوری به او نه بگویم که کارم را از دست ندم . چه جوری بهش جواب رد بدم که بعدا آبروم را نبره . برای همه اینها زنان باید خودشون را تا حدودی جای مردان میذاشتن چون در غیر این صورت باید هزینه پرداخت میکردن اما چنین چیزی لزوما برای مردان صدق نمیکرده . مردان چون از جایگاه اجتماعی و اقتصادی بالاتری نسبت به زنان برخوردار بودن در چنین مواردی نباید چندان نگران این میبودن که زنان چه حسی نسبت به رفتارشان دارن . مثلا یک مدیر مرد در یک شرکت با فراغ خاطر میتونسته کارمند زن را آزارجنسی بده این کارمند زن بوده که باید فکر میکرده چه جوری واکنش بدم که کارم را از دست ندم، نکنه واکنشم باعث بشه عصبانی بشه و غیره در حالیکه برای آن مرد که در جایگاه قدرت بوده تنها چیز مهم به دست آوردن خواستش بوده . اتفاقی که با جنبشی مثل افتاد این بود که حالا مردان باید به این فکر کنن که رفتار و گفتارشون چه حسی را در زنان ایجاد میکنه . حالا مردها باید خودشان را جای زنان بگذارن وگرنه باید هزینه بدن . این نگرانی از هزینه دادن در اینکه ما مجبور باشیم خودمون را کمی جای دیگران بذاریم تاثیر زیادی داره . دیگه فقط مهم نیست که اونچه که میخوای را بگیری بلکه اینکه چه جوری اون را گرفتی و طرف با چه حسی خواسته تو را برآورده کرده مهم میشه . این یه تغییر بزرگ در روابط زن و مرد به طور گسترده ایجاد میکنه . اینکه مردان حالا باید یاد بگیرن که این چیزها را در نظر بگیرن خیلی گام بزرگیه و برای مردان هم خوبه . این فقط زنان نیستن که ازین مسئله سود میبرن این هوش عاطفی و حساسیت به احساسات طرف مقابل داینامیک روابط انسانی را بهتر میکنه . * مسلما وقتی از مردان و زنان حرف میزنم منظورم این نیست همه مردان و همه زنان اینجورین و مردها همه آزاردهنده جنسی و زنان همه قربانی بودن . بلکه منظورم اون تجربه زیستی زن و مرد هست که یک میانگین رفتار و واکنش را ایجاد میکنه در جوامع . مینیسم column1: 267565;instagram;2018-10-30 07:00:59;FALSE;"very proud mum. my partner and son came into the clinic and had lunch with me today. it was a welcome visit. i miss my family. my partner brought in my therapy dog toby who i hadn’t seen for a week. he went bezerk when he saw me!!!! he ran around in circles almost talking he was so excited. it’s not possible to have him stay with me here in the clinic even though he would be allowed because he’s an australian kelpie who are an extremely active breed and it would be cruel. i just couldn’t give him the exercise that he needs and is used to on the farm. he’d miss his chickens. it was great to spend time with him. i enjoyed so much patting him.

the great news my son had was that he had signed a lease on a shared house with four friends. that is really significant as he is autistic. he has just finished his first year of university while living in an apartment that we took turns to share with him. he found his niche at uni and made some great friends
column2: an achievement in itself and they asked him to share a house with him. together they organised themselves and found a great federation terrace house in inner-city redfern in sydney only twenty minutes walk from their uni. he has overcome so many of the social challenges that autistic people face in this achievement. i am so proud of him. he struggled all the way through primary school finding it hard to make friends. it was a bit better in high school but he has really blossomed at uni. the course itself is his passion so that helps. he is mixing with people as obsessed with film and drama as himself so commonality is so important. it’s a great relief to us his parents. i’m feeling very positive about his 2019. https://youwillbearwitness.com/2018/10/29/very-proud-mum/ #ptsdawareness #ptsd #trauma #doitfordolly #ptsdsurvivor #peterfox #ptsdsurvivor #ptsdrecovery #stopracism #stopbullying #stopchildabuse #cardinalpell #metoo";;en;#ptsdawareness

column1: as a #survivor i strive everyday to not allow my past to define me. to make moves that are reflective of whom god would call me to be. to never be held back by someone else’s wants and opinions. it wasn’t just physical for me. it was emotional
column5: it was financial. i know the feeling of being dragged
column9: having a gun held to me
column10: sleeping with a gun in our bed
column12: my money being withheld and demanded
column13: told where i could work and for how long
column16: what to wear and not wear
column17: what my own children could/couldn’t do

column1: 267673;instagram;2018-10-30 04:47:57;FALSE;"京都にある性被害の自助グループ「mint（ミント）」11月の活動予定のお知らせです❤︎
女性として生きる中で感じていることを気軽に話せる場所です。批判やアドバイスはせず、話すほうも聞くほうもお互いにありのままで受け止めます。主に性的なトラウマを抱える女性を対象としていますが、性被害のご経験の有無に関わらず女性として生きてきた中で向き合いたいことやお話ししたいことがあるときに足を運んでみてくださいね。
京都駅中央改札口より徒歩約12分

会場へのアクセスなど自助グループについて詳細はプロフィール欄（ @selfhelpgroup_mint ）ホームページの「self help group」をご覧ください。
遠方の方や直接会うことに抵抗がある場合はオンラインサロンでもお話しすることができます。近況を話すmeetingやworkshopに加え、ご自身の体験を綴っていただいたりお気に入りの写真や音楽を共有したり当事者のためのサロンです。
オンラインサロンについての詳細はプロフィール欄（ @selfhelpgroup_mint ）ホームページの「online salon」をご覧ください。

column1: 267692;instagram;2018-10-30 03:50:46;FALSE;"i saw a post that stated that chess was a sexist game and is anti-feminist.... i don’t know what liberal-pea brain-psychopathic-mentally obtuse-#metoo-feminist came up with this idiotic conclusion.
chess is pro-women if anything and in fact if you examine it very carefully
column2: it has a profound life message for women.

column1: that’s 14 pieces (different life variables- impersonal lines of defence and protection for the king)
these different variables can move in different ways. what it shows if when your darling (your king) is in hard times
column2: he might seek the help of several strangers (pawns)
column3: one time moves. if they don’t work he will seek the help of a religious leader
column5: lawyers or anyone he feels he can trust for guidance..

column1: they can only make one directional moves... they won’t move in a way outside their comfort zone to help.
and here is where the profound lesson is learned.. the queen stands by the king
column2: and when he can’t seem to advance and is only progressing one move at a time
column3: it’s the job of the queen to fight
column4: move in every direction in order to protect the king. when everyone else failed to protect the king it is the job of a single queen to fight all odds
column8: keeping harm at bay while the king does what he can to survive and advance. the game ends not when the check-mate occurs
column9: it ends when the queen failed.

column1: so crazy feminists and actually all women... play a little chess and learn your role as your king’s queen. take care of him
column2: be strong when he is weak
column4: protect him and encourage him... struggle is a burden to be shared and as emotionally superior creatures (no offence men) realize that when everyone and everything has failed him
column5: you have to step up and be his army of one. if you fail him you ultimately failed yourself. be wise and fight  for a man who loves you
column6: not every bozo is worth this level of loyalty. find your true love someone who treats you like a queen and treat him and protect him like a king.

column1: 267706;instagram;2018-10-30 04:02:40;FALSE;"claire mccaskill is the democratic nominee for us senate from missouri!

▪️ economic issues - mccaskill did not support president trump when he visited missouri to promote his tax bill. she said that she could support a tax bill put together “in a bipartisan way” and the reason why she rejected trump’s bill was because it would mainly help rich st. louis suburbanites. ▪️ immigration - she voted for the dream act
column2: which gives undocumented immigrants a pathway to citizenship and has put protecting dreamers a top priority. she opposed trump administration’s policy on separating families who crossed the border illegally.

column1: ▪️ healthcare - 100% lifetime rating from planned parenthood in 2017 and american public health association also gave her 100% rating in 2016 for her positions on healthcare issues the previous year.
she voted for obamacare. in april 2017
column2: she expressed her opposition to a single-payer healthcare system
column3: saying it is too expensive and not realistic. she also introduced the health care options for all act
column4: where people living in counties with no health-care exchanges would be able to buy coverage through the dc small business exchange.

column2: in woke color: prabal gurung’s runways have become do-not-miss events. his february 2017 show
column3: with its game-changing finale with a parade of body-diverse models in feminist-slogan t-shirts
column4: was one of the seminal political moments of a very political season. in the fall
column5: gurung lured feminist icon gloria steinem to her first-ever fashion week show
column6: giving him distinction as one of the most “woke” front rows of the fashion weeks. on feb. 12
column7: #metoo founder tarana burke was front and center
column8: and gurung closed his show with a parade of models walking without music en masse to the photographers’ pit carrying white roses
column9: a sign of solidarity with #metoo that was also used at the grammys. the attention to activism
column11: shouldn’t minimize how consistently good gurung’s fashion is. the himalayan designer has looked to regional asian cultures effectively in the past and turned to the matriarchal mosuo tribe of china as part of this season’s story. the knits
column12: with their tribal motifs and oversize silhouette
column13: were dressed up with tribal sequined skirts and woolly hem details; other prabal signatures like the open-cut ruffled frocks also appeared. the rainbow of hues gave the collection an optimistic overall impression (especially in the mixed florals) that felt fresh and in keeping with his empowerment ethos. power

column1: 267775;instagram;2018-10-30 02:29:18;FALSE;"...what you tell yourself matters... i made it to #orangetheory today for #hellweek and totally forgot. i thought i was going to die but i survived 🤣 i burned 613 cals 🍊 and 39 splat points 🍊
as i was working out i realized i say in my head somethings to keep me pushing when i feel like i cant.
i tell myself i am beautiful
column3: and that i am healthy. i tell myself these things because... 1. iam forced to look at myself in the mirror. i struggle with thinking i am beautiful. so i tell myself that because i hope to over come that one day. i believe a lot of women struggle with this and its its something we dont tell ourselves enough. you are beautiful! anyone else saying #metoo ?!?! 2. i tell myself i am healthy and 130lbs because that is where i am determine to be. i truely believe if you tell your mind something it will do it. so every time i get to the place i want to quit that is what i tell myself.

column1: my mind has helped me accomplish soo much. (48 hour home birth unmedicated) so i know its a journey but i keep telling myself what i need to accomplish my goals.
who else tells themselves what they need to hear to keep pushing forward?! #kidsq #kidt #shadest #sunglassest #familyt #familyq #momlifet #momlifequoted #momlifetho

column1: 267808;instagram;2018-10-30 01:52:42;FALSE;"@regran_ed from @talk2spirit -  ptsd stands for post traumatic stress disorder. it literally means the negative effects (i.e. the ""stress"") a person experiences after (i.e. ""post"") a traumatic event. trauma can include any number of things - from witnessing a traumatic event
column2: to being the victim of a crime or accident
column3: to being in a combat/conflict zone - either as a solider or a civilian. ptsd is real and if left untreated can be even more traumatic than the event itself. anyone can develop ptsd
column4: including children. many people walk around with ptsd for decades without even realizing that they are sick and in need of healthcare. if you or someone you know has suffered a traumatic event
column5: or are suffering any of these symptoms

column1: 267835;instagram;2018-10-30 01:15:19;FALSE;"it was such a great honor of mine to be able to be a guest speaker  at the felony mental health court graduation  ceremony last week.
i had the pleasure of speaking about the importance of goal setting as it relates to mental health.  i was also able to bring awareness to rape & molestation
column2: eating disorders while encouraging the graduates to know there is life after adversity regardless of their dress size.

column1: the program offers people who have mental disorder a chance to participate in the program instead of going to jail for a crime they normally would haven't committed under normal circumstances.  the fmhc carefully  screens each defendant's case before making the determination on rather to allow them to participate in the program or not.  upon successfully completing the program some cases are completely dismissed.

did you know that approximately 20% of the jail population have a mental disorder?  the fmhc offers each hand selected participant the chance they need to be a thriving member of the community. this program proves that some people just need help instead of incarceration.

column1: 267839;instagram;2018-10-30 01:17:16;FALSE;"~~~spreadinglovespreadinglight~~~ article installment part 2 ~~~”living in a place of surrender” by claire jones
column2: thrive global~~~ america beckoned to me through stories and through my television screen. longing to be there rather than in my own unhappy life situation
column3: i often stood on the water’s edge of my favorite beach
column4: willing my spirit across the choppy
column7: the moment was anticlimactic when it finally came. in this way
column8: i came to deeply believe i could control my life if i wished hard enough for it to go my way.

column2: this magical thinking came to a stop over the last year when i became ill. in fighting to heal myself i found i had to release willful thinking and pseudo control. at first i fought to take charge of the situation by using my old survival tactics. however
column3: none of them worked. i finally surrendered all of the power
column5: letting go to the natural workings of life. in so doing
column6: i was able to rise above the many crises
column7: which unfolded because of my health problem. today
column8: living in a place of surrender is allowing me to reshape my life in positive.

column2: the first thing i do in my morning routine is to surrender my life situation to the powers that be. this is not an easy path to take
column3: and it might not be a path most would follow
column4: but it is working for me. it takes enormous self discipline and consistent practice.~~~ final install tomorrow morn~~~#surrender #faith #change #writing #writingcommnity #writersofinstagram #immigrants #vision #positive #positivevibes #encouragement #motivational #inspirational #womensupportingwomen #womenwriters #blackwomenwriters #personalblog #selfimprovement #inspiringothers #clarity #awareness #presence #yoga #yogainspiration #yogacommunity #women #metoo #survivor #mindfulness #spiritual🙏🏽for likes and follows!❤️✨✨👍🏽💫";;en;#faith

column1: 267910;instagram;2018-10-29 23:43:41;FALSE;you never think it’s going to happen to you
column2: until it does. almost 1 year ago i found myself being pressed against a wall living in a body which i no longer owned. i entered a state of such perpetual ptsd
column3: i started having blackout seizures. i cried my eyes out every night in the shower
column4: so that no one could hear me. i was afraid nobody would believe me. i was afraid i’d be treated like i was damaged. but i wasnt raised to give up. for i am convinced that neither death
column6: or neither height nor depth can separate us from love. my spine was formed with elasticity so that i could handle both the downs and the ups. i refuse to let the world harden me. to live wholeheartedly means assessing the risks of vulnerability & doing that shit anyway. i will say the names of all the victims before me till my fucking lungs give out. que pa eso mi mamá crió una berraca. #whyididntreport #metoo;;en;#WhyIDidntReport

column1: it shouldn't be hard to imagine that someone who's endured prolonged trauma at the total control of another person might wrestle with concepts of safety
column4: and reciprocity. whether the trauma was in childhood or a bit later in life
column5: no relationship goes untouched by trauma's effects. some are even so subtle that many don't notice until they've snowballed into a much bigger issue.

column1: survivors of chronic abuse have had their trust completely obliterated
column2: oftentimes along with the idea that counting on or getting close to anyone is a good idea. they may push people away
column5: or (conversely) attach too tightly to the one person they feel they can rely on. (sometimes that person may even be unsafe.) some may feel they deserve to be hurt and accept toxic/abusive 'friends'; others believe 'regular' people would find them to be too broken or too much to handle.

column2: they may find themselves wanting so badly for someone to save them and make everything okay that they just never stop searching for a rescuer. others may cling fiercely to people out of innocence - a deep
column3: aching fear of being abandoned - to the point any absence feels like neglect. and neglect reminds them of trauma. and that's just too painful to risk.

column5: strangers - they can all be wrought with so many unhealthy or unbalanced dynamics -- the most heartbreaking of which being when a survivor's entire network is made up of solely toxic/unsafe individuals. because it's all they've ever known
column6: it feels so normal. how were they to know any better or want something they don't know exists?

column2: there's good news. it is possible to understand what's going on in your relationships - to learn what's healthy and what stems from trauma. you deserve safe
column4: balanced relationships and no less. therapy
column5: particularly dbt which has an entire section on ""interpersonal effectiveness""
column6: makes these absolutely attainable goals and we'd love to help you reach them. you're worth that much.

column1: i constantly see ""men get raped too"" pop up everywhere.
why is there a ""too"" there? men get raped. this is a huge problem
column3: and it deserves it's own platform. the ""too"" only shows up to silence women when the conversation is centered around women like me who are survivors of sexual assault. the people who use that ""too"" are actually doing male and female survivors a huge disservice
column4: they are feeding the sexual assault silencing machine society has created. you see
column5: they are using a serious issue like male rape to silence women instead of working on giving it its own platform. this has a massively adverse effect. it trivialises male rape instead of amplifying it. which goes to say a majority of the people using it are not victims themselves. and that is deeply upsetting because not enough male survivors come forward
column6: there are not enough platforms for them
column7: there is certainly not nearly enough support and they need it. if people were showing up on male rape conversations saying
column8: ""women get raped too"" i would be the first person to shut that down
column9: because how dare they belittle any survivor's story that way? our trauma is not your silencing weapon

column2: i have the utmost respect to war veterans and in no way is this post aimed to play down the horrors they have lived through. but i would like to talk quickly about post traumatic stress disorder and one of the most common misconceptions people have about it
column3: which is that it only really affects war veterans. this couldn't be further from the truth. the reality is that ptsd can affect many groups of people. many
column4: many victims of sexual abuse have ptsd. i personally have spoken to some on this account and some have not had their ptsd taken as seriously as it should have been taken because of the myth that it solely affects soldiers. anyone can have ptsd. many firefighters have it
column5: people who have had painful surgeries
column10: symptoms may not even present themselves until months or even years after the traumatic event. ptsd is a really serious mental illness and to be honest it's something i need to learn more about
column11: but i hope anyone reading this realizes that it's more common than you think.

column1: 267979;instagram;2018-10-29 22:19:47;FALSE;"what does eating healthy and exercise do for you??!!... in the past 12 months i’ve lost 6kg probably more of fat as i’ve also put on muscle which is heavier and weight loss and or muscle gain seems to be everyone’s focus. but is that important?! or is there more?! so much more exercise can do for us?! what we look like on the outside is something but what it does for your mind and body on the inside is so much more. returning to a regular exercise routine where i never go 2 days without a workout is a huge part of why i can say i “had” anxiety ..that and meditation.  without going too much into what i’d been running from and had taken me out of the game i think just #metoo is enough. now i’m still human i can say i feel uncomfortable sometimes but usually in a new environment learning or pushing myself and i now know it’s growth or excitement. before it was constant debilitating fear. fear of everything
column2: mostly of being caught out being afraid... i was supposed to be strong and have it all together. now my memory is better. i can concentrate. i feel optimistic
column3: joyful and happy about life’s future. a recent change in work that had me having to rely on family in transition again would have in the past left me bed ridden in guilt and shame that i couldn’t do it all myself... instead this time  i was grateful for the help and did the work to change things and now have more work and getting more each week that i love. no need to borrow any more and next week i start paying back and i know i will pay back every cent i’ve ever borrowed and have learnt  that community is so so important. we’re not meant to do this alone. i have more resilience now thanks to pushing my body and training even when i don’t feel like it. i have more energy now. i can get up and jump around like a kid again often having friends say you’re like a child... yep and proud of it! it took alot of work to find that kid again.  when i started this 12 months detox everything exhausted me. i’d lost my spark

i must have been six when it happened. me and my family were preparing to pick our dad from the airport. he was coming back home after a long period of time
column2: working his way off overseas. we were so excited. we hired a driver to drive us to the airport. he seemed friendly at first. our family had heard of him since he belonged to our community
column3: so there was an instant trust. he said he loved playing with kids when he saw me and insisted if he could take me on a walk. i agreed because he gave me candies. my mom in her naivety
column4: agreed. it was my grandma who felt something was wrong. she just didn't get good vibes from him. she was stern but my mother's kindness melted her  as well. we started walking and he took me to an abandoned place. i thought he was tired and wants a break. he later called me and made me sit on his lap. he started off by fondling me and kissing me forcefully. i was naive and innocent to the point where i thought he was showing his affection. he then slid his hand underneath my frock and touched me inappropriately for a few minutes. when i started crying
column5: he hushed me and gave me a candy. that night
column6: i couldn't sleep. i didn't know what happened
column7: but i felt unclean. something inside me as a six year old changed. in the coming days
column8: my behaviour changed and i turned to isolation. my grandma smelled my quietness and kept on questioning about the guy. i was so scared to speak up because i didn't even know if what happened was wrong. i thought i would make an issue out of a mole. it was only later i realised the difference between right and wrong touch. people need to realize that #metoo isn't just a hashtag
